<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-11T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-11T08:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/45:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-11T10:00:00-03:00">July 11, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:15 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. Embassy’s 40, July 2, 2 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d520fn31">Not
                                printed.</note> The President informed me yesterday afternoon that
                            he had instructed the Minister of Finance to issue an administrative
                            order canceling in its entirety the fine levied by the Inspector of
                            Banks on National City Bank.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>